ature and Georg Grote is Lecturer in German history, both at University College Dublin. Mary Cosgrove is Lecturer in German at the University of Edinburgh.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCollective memoryzGermany. 0aGroup identityzGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 4aEnglish & American Literature. 4aFilm & Theatre. 4aGerman Literature. 4aModern History. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  a20th Century Germany.  aCultural Debates.  aEthnicity.  aFamily Narrative.  aGender.  aGenerations.  aGerman Memory Contests.  aHistoriography.  aHolocaust.  aIdentity.  aMemory.  aNational Socialism.  aPublic Discourse.  aTrauma.1 aBoa, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCosgrove, Mary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCosgrove, Mary, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFiedler, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFritzsche, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFuchs, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFuchs, Anne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGelbin, Cathy S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGelbin, Cathy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrote, Georg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLong, J. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLong, Jonathan J, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLorenz, Dagmar C. G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMichaels, Jennifer E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 